The van was carrying 12 people from South Carolina to Atlanta for a heavy metal show Monday night . 
  The driver of the 15-passenger van 'apparently fell asleep and allowed the vehicle to leave the road and down an embankment  . 
  Members of the Atlanta-based band Khaotika and the Huntsville, Alabama-based Wormreich were in the van . 
  Three people were killed and eight were injured in the crash . 
  The van and trailer went off Interstate 85 near Commerce about 7am Monday . 
  The three men who died were ejected from the vehicle and the driver was not injured . 
 